Package org.mariuszgromada.math.mxparser

Class Function

java.lang.Object
org.mariuszgromada.math.mxparser.PrimitiveElement
org.mariuszgromada.math.mxparser.Function
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Function extends PrimitiveElement implements Serializable
Function class provides possibility to define user functions. Functions can be used in further processing by any expression, dependent or recursive argument, function, etc... For example:
  • 'f(x) = sin(x)'
  • 'g(x,y) = sin(x)+cos(y)'
  • 'h(x,y = f(x)+g(y,x)'
  • in general 'f(x1,x2,...,xn)' where x1,...,xn are arguments

When creating a function you should avoid names reserved as parser keywords, in general words known in mathematical language as function names, operators (for example: sin, cos, +, -, pi, e, etc...). Please be informed that after associating the constant with the expression, function or dependent/recursive argument its name will be recognized by the parser as reserved key word. It means that it could not be the same as any other key word known by the parser for this particular expression.

    • cloneForThreadSafe

      public Function cloneForThreadSafe()
      Creates a completely independent 1-1 clone that can be safely used by a separate thread. If the cloned element contains references to other elements (e.g. arguments, functions, constants), then they will also be cloned and the newly created element will contain references to the corresponding clones. Important - the API allows you to extract all these clones.
      Returns:
      Cloned object.
